WEBVTT

00:02.240 --> 00:04.197
[♪♪♪]

00:04.760 --> 00:11.599
ANNOUNCER:
<i>This is the story of two sisters:</i>
<i>Jessica Tate and Mary Campbell.</i>

00:11.800 --> 00:16.079
<i>Jessica lives in a neighbourhood</i>
<i>known as rich.</i>

00:16.280 --> 00:17.953
<i>Jessica likes life.</i>

00:18.160 --> 00:21.039
<i>The only thing about life</i>
<i>she would change, if she could,</i>

00:21.240 --> 00:23.755
<i>is that she would</i>
<i>set it all to music.</i>

00:25.040 --> 00:28.829
<i>The Tates have more secrets</i>
<i>than they do money.</i>

00:31.440 --> 00:34.638
<i>We're approaching</i>
<i>Mary Campbell's house.</i>

00:36.400 --> 00:37.959
<i>Mary, too, likes life.</i>

00:38.160 --> 00:42.040
<i>Unfortunately, life doesn't seem</i>
<i>to be too crazy about her.</i>

00:42.240 --> 00:46.951
<i>As you can see, the Campbells</i>
<i>don't have nearly as much money</i>
<i>as the Tates.</i>

00:47.720 --> 00:51.396
<i>They do, however,</i>
<i>have as many secrets.</i>

00:55.200 --> 00:57.237
<i>In last week's episode of</i> Soap,

00:57.440 --> 00:59.830
<i>Jessica admitted her affair</i>
<i>to Chester,</i>

01:00.040 --> 01:02.874
<i>but Chester wouldn't admit</i>
<i>his affairs to Jessica.</i>

01:03.080 --> 01:04.593
<i>So Jessica walked out on him.</i>

01:04.800 --> 01:08.077
<i>Corinne caught Peter nibbling</i>
<i>another woman's ear</i>

01:08.280 --> 01:11.717
<i>and told him if she ever caught him</i>
<i>fooling around, she would kill him.</i>

01:11.920 --> 01:15.357
<i>Jodie, who tried to kill himself</i>
<i>because Dennis left him,</i>

01:15.560 --> 01:17.119
<i>woke up alive.</i>

01:17.320 --> 01:18.320
<i>Confused?</i>

01:18.520 --> 01:22.594
<i>You won't be after</i>
<i>this week's episode of</i> Soap.

01:23.640 --> 01:25.916
<i>We begin this week's</i>
<i>episode of</i> Soap

01:26.120 --> 01:30.433
<i>the morning after Jessica</i>
<i>walked out on Chester.</i>

01:35.640 --> 01:37.359
Good morning, Benson.
Good morning.

01:38.920 --> 01:40.434
Looking for someone?

01:40.640 --> 01:43.917
Huh? Who in the world would
I be looking for, Benson?

01:44.120 --> 01:45.315
Mrs. Tate.

01:45.520 --> 01:46.960
Why would I be looking
for Mrs. Tate?

01:47.160 --> 01:48.958
Because she didn't
spend the night here.

01:49.160 --> 01:52.517
What are you talking about, Benson?
Of course she spent the night here.

01:52.720 --> 01:54.154
Oh, yeah? Then where is she?

01:55.280 --> 01:58.398
Uh, she went out early this morning.

01:58.600 --> 02:00.319
Mrs. Tate don't leave early
no morning.

02:00.520 --> 02:03.672
Mrs. Tate can't find her shoes
much before noon.

02:04.600 --> 02:09.231
It just so happens that this morning
she got up very early and went out.

02:09.440 --> 02:11.160
Good morning, Daddy.
Good morning, princess.

02:11.360 --> 02:13.556
Good morning, Benson.
Mm.

02:14.480 --> 02:15.630
I've gotta go, Daddy.

02:15.840 --> 02:17.600
Oh, tell mother I won't
be home this evening.

02:17.680 --> 02:20.912
I'm flying to Washington to cover
Congressman McCallam's
press conference.

02:21.120 --> 02:23.760
And then she's gonna
cover McCallam.

02:26.600 --> 02:28.193
[LAUGHING]

02:28.400 --> 02:30.835
Shut up, Benson.

02:31.040 --> 02:34.033
Well, well, well.
Look who's here.

02:34.240 --> 02:36.197
Oh, Benson, I've got to have a cup
of coffee this morning.

02:36.400 --> 02:37.400
[GASPS]

02:37.560 --> 02:38.994
What a night I had.

02:42.520 --> 02:45.831
You know, Chester, when people
get angry and storm off and say:

02:46.040 --> 02:50.398
"That's it. I've had it. I'm leaving,"
I wonder where it is they go.

02:50.960 --> 02:52.280
Thank you, Benson.

02:52.480 --> 02:53.880
Well, you see, I went to the beach

02:54.080 --> 02:56.436
because, you know,
I thought that would be
a nice, quiet place to think.

02:56.640 --> 03:01.840
But, Chester, it was freezing cold and
then this seagull kept attacking me.

03:02.040 --> 03:04.191
So, of course, I couldn't stay
on the beach

03:04.400 --> 03:07.950
and I went to an all-night movie,
but, I mean, I couldn't stay there
because of that man.

03:08.160 --> 03:09.992
So I just...

03:10.200 --> 03:11.395
What man?

03:11.600 --> 03:13.717
Oh, this man that sat next to me.

03:13.920 --> 03:16.151
Chester, I was the only one
in the entire movie

03:16.360 --> 03:17.760
and then this man came in

03:17.960 --> 03:20.475
and with all those empty seats,
where do you think he sat?

03:20.680 --> 03:22.558
Next to you.
Right.

03:22.760 --> 03:27.073
And even though the theatre
was terribly warm, the entire time
he kept on his, uh...

03:27.280 --> 03:30.159
Trench coat.
Right. Yes.

03:30.360 --> 03:33.034
And I mean, Chester,
if that wasn't bad enough,

03:33.240 --> 03:35.596
I couldn't even hear the movie
because of his...

03:35.800 --> 03:38.440
Heavy breathing?

03:38.640 --> 03:41.030
Right. Chester, do you know him?

03:45.240 --> 03:47.436
No.

03:47.640 --> 03:50.280
Well, by that time it was
6-something in the morning

03:50.480 --> 03:53.791
and the sun was coming up,
and, oh, Chester, it was wonderful.

03:54.000 --> 03:58.119
Well, Jessica, I'm glad that
you came to your senses
and decided to come home.

03:58.320 --> 04:01.233
Oh, I didn't come
to my senses, Chester.

04:01.440 --> 04:03.511
Well, I mean,
I did come to my senses,

04:03.720 --> 04:07.794
but I think I may have come
to different senses than
you would have liked.

04:08.000 --> 04:09.559
What are you talking about, Jessica?

04:09.760 --> 04:15.040
Well, you see, Chester,
I know what you've done,

04:15.240 --> 04:17.880
and I have decided to...

04:18.079 --> 04:20.435
Well, "forgive" wouldn't be
exactly the right word

04:20.640 --> 04:25.840
because I'm not gonna forgive you,
but to put it on the shelf for now.

04:26.800 --> 04:29.713
But, Chester,
if it ever happens again,

04:29.920 --> 04:32.799
I'm afraid I won't be able
to put it on the shelf.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.356
By then, the shelf will be full.

04:43.840 --> 04:46.674
Why are you standing there
grinning, Benson?

04:46.880 --> 04:52.717
I don't know what I love more,
her sticking it to you
or you getting stuck.

04:54.680 --> 04:56.637
[♪♪♪]

05:01.200 --> 05:03.431
Nice how we're both getting out
on the same day.

05:03.640 --> 05:05.597
This way, neither of us
gets left alone.

05:05.800 --> 05:07.234
Yeah.

05:07.440 --> 05:10.831
Hey, kiddo, you're leaving
the hospital, you're not entering.

05:11.040 --> 05:13.953
You got your moods confused here.
What's the matter?

05:14.160 --> 05:16.994
This may sound crazy,
but I kind of don't wanna leave.

05:18.000 --> 05:21.437
Of course you don't wanna leave,
because it's safe here.

05:21.640 --> 05:23.552
Barney, when I came in here,
I had a life.

05:23.760 --> 05:26.514
I knew who I was,
what I was gonna do, what I wanted.

05:26.720 --> 05:28.200
I had someone.

05:28.400 --> 05:29.470
Now I don't know.

05:29.680 --> 05:31.990
Listen, kiddo, we're not so different.

05:32.200 --> 05:34.157
I also have to go out there alone.

05:34.360 --> 05:37.159
But neither of us
knows what tomorrow is.

05:37.360 --> 05:41.957
And I'll tell you something, Jodie,
neither does anybody else.

05:42.920 --> 05:46.709
Nobody knows. Robert Redford
doesn't know what tomorrow is.

05:47.400 --> 05:49.790
They could decide tomorrow,
nobody with moles works.

05:50.000 --> 05:51.798
He's finished.

05:54.440 --> 05:57.592
But what we do know
is that when we're born,

05:57.800 --> 06:02.955
we're given just one thing: time.

06:03.520 --> 06:07.275
Of course, if you're a Rockefeller,
you also get property.

06:08.160 --> 06:10.994
But most of us just
get time, Jodie. Use it.

06:11.200 --> 06:13.271
Enjoy it. Me?

06:13.480 --> 06:15.551
I'm gonna learn French.
What?

06:15.760 --> 06:18.434
That's right. When I get out of here,
I'm gonna enrol.
I'm signing up right away.

06:18.640 --> 06:22.111
I'm gonna learn French.
And maybe I'll go someday to Paris.

06:22.320 --> 06:26.439
And if I die first, who knows,
maybe God is named Pierre.

06:27.440 --> 06:28.794
Hi.

06:29.000 --> 06:33.517
Hi. Ohh. Nurse Beautiful.

06:33.880 --> 06:35.280
Oh, watch yourself, sweetheart.

06:35.480 --> 06:37.233
In my street clothes, I'm a tiger here.

06:37.440 --> 06:39.909
Oh, I don't know what I'm
gonna do without you two.

06:40.120 --> 06:41.600
What? Come on.

06:41.800 --> 06:43.359
An old man and a homosexual?

06:43.560 --> 06:46.553
Whatever comes next
has gotta be better.

06:47.480 --> 06:51.110
All right, it's time for
my last bathroom attempt.

06:51.320 --> 06:54.597
I feel like Livingstone
setting out for Africa.

06:56.720 --> 06:59.599
I'm really gonna miss you.
Well, I'll kind of miss you too.

06:59.800 --> 07:01.359
You will?
Yeah.

07:01.560 --> 07:04.029
Why?
Hey, you're a nice person.

07:04.240 --> 07:05.799
I'll miss a nice person.

07:06.200 --> 07:07.429
Oh.

07:07.960 --> 07:11.510
Well, uh, maybe, uh, sometime we'll
have dinner together or something.

07:11.720 --> 07:13.871
Sure. When?
Oh, I don't know.

07:14.080 --> 07:15.080
Tonight?
Tonight?

07:15.280 --> 07:17.272
Wonderful, 8:00,
I'll give you my address.

07:17.480 --> 07:18.480
Wait a second.

07:18.680 --> 07:21.593
How about French food?
I know a terrific French restaurant.

07:21.800 --> 07:23.200
Listen, this is just dinner,
you understand?

07:23.400 --> 07:24.400
Sure. Dinner.

07:24.560 --> 07:25.960
I mean, we'll have a meal together.

07:26.160 --> 07:27.355
Right. No dancing.

07:27.560 --> 07:29.560
This is not like it's
a bona fide date or anything.

07:29.600 --> 07:30.829
Right.
It's a meal.

07:31.040 --> 07:32.040
Right. A meal.
Right.

07:32.200 --> 07:33.714
We will eat and we will talk.

07:33.920 --> 07:36.879
Right.
And then, we'll go to bed.

07:42.320 --> 07:45.358
Woo-ha.

07:46.480 --> 07:49.314
No "woo-ha," it's a meal.

07:49.520 --> 07:51.671
I mean, we'll just have a meal
together, that's all.

07:51.880 --> 07:54.793
Sure, it's just a meal. Come on,
Jodie, it's like me and French.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.151
You never know
when you might use it.

08:00.160 --> 08:02.277
So you got somebody
to pick you up?

08:02.480 --> 08:05.154
Yeah. My mother's downstairs.
Ah. Okay.

08:06.360 --> 08:08.033
Barney, I, uh...

08:08.240 --> 08:11.074
I hate to say goodbye to you.
Well, it doesn't thrill me, either.

08:11.280 --> 08:14.114
I mean, besides being
wise and caring...

08:14.320 --> 08:16.551
Please, Jodie...
No, no, no. You're gonna listen.

08:16.760 --> 08:18.717
I mean, you've talked plenty.

08:18.920 --> 08:22.231
Barney, you've made me
feel terrific.

08:22.440 --> 08:24.591
You're the first person
I've ever met

08:24.800 --> 08:28.350
who put aside what I was
and just simply liked me.

08:28.560 --> 08:32.952
Never in all my life have I ever
met anyone like you, Barney Gerber.

08:35.080 --> 08:36.275
Well, now I guess...

08:36.480 --> 08:38.756
Don't say it, I don't wanna
hear it. No goodbyes.

08:38.960 --> 08:42.510
Because, while I was
in the bathroom, I, uh...

08:42.720 --> 08:46.157
I wrote down my address
and my phone number.

08:48.840 --> 08:51.230
Well, what else was
I gonna do in there?

08:52.360 --> 08:56.070
Now, I want you to
go and write likewise.

08:56.280 --> 08:59.990
Listen, Jodie, I realise that people
often exchange these things.

09:00.200 --> 09:03.318
And then, months later,
they find the scrap of paper

09:03.520 --> 09:06.115
and they, uh... They put
their chewing gum in it.

09:06.320 --> 09:08.915
But that's not gonna
happen here. No, sir.

09:09.120 --> 09:13.080
Because I don't let somebody I like
get out of my life.

09:13.280 --> 09:15.317
And in the second place,

09:15.520 --> 09:19.480
having my dentures, it would be
very reckless for me to chew gum.

09:21.400 --> 09:22.675
Ah.

09:22.880 --> 09:26.078
Hey, you're a terrific guy, Jodie.

09:26.280 --> 09:28.511
Go. Be happy.

09:29.080 --> 09:30.719
Hey, you can, you know.

09:30.920 --> 09:34.311
Come on. It's up to you.
It's just a choice.

09:34.520 --> 09:38.560
Look, you'll find another guy.
Or you'll find a girl.

09:38.760 --> 09:43.039
Or you'll find no one.
It doesn't matter.

09:43.760 --> 09:46.434
You got you.

09:47.120 --> 09:50.909
And you also got
the sunshine, huh?

09:51.120 --> 09:53.157
And you got the flowers.

09:53.360 --> 09:58.389
You got music,
and once in a while,

09:58.800 --> 10:00.996
whenever you want,

10:02.200 --> 10:04.237
you got Barney Gerber.

10:06.000 --> 10:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:15.960 --> 10:17.360
I'll see you, Barney.

10:18.240 --> 10:20.471
Yeah, I'll see you, Jodie.

10:21.440 --> 10:23.397
[♪♪♪]

10:27.760 --> 10:30.992
Look at him. He's getting
ready for the next shift.

10:31.200 --> 10:34.432
Ava, Corinne's gonna be here
any second, so you gotta go.
Sorry, baby.

10:34.640 --> 10:37.109
Oh, please, I love it.
Hit and run. Very romantic.

10:37.320 --> 10:39.961
Next time, perhaps we could wait
until I put down my tennis racket?

10:40.040 --> 10:41.076
[KNOCKING]

10:41.280 --> 10:43.590
Oh, there she is. Goodbye.
What? Are you crazy?

10:43.800 --> 10:45.314
I can't leave here half-dressed.

10:45.520 --> 10:46.840
The whole club will know,

10:47.040 --> 10:50.033
and in two minutes, my husband will
take our joint savings and my Jaguar
and leave in a rocket.

10:50.240 --> 10:52.357
Okay, then. In the bathroom.
Please, but be quiet.

10:52.560 --> 10:56.156
No. I thought I would sing something
from <i>Carmen.</i>

11:00.040 --> 11:02.635
Corinne's mother. Uh...

11:02.840 --> 11:04.752
Corinne's not here.
Oh, good.

11:04.960 --> 11:06.758
I was hoping I'd find you alone.

11:06.960 --> 11:08.110
Uh, look, Jess...

11:08.320 --> 11:10.676
Please, Peter, I've got to
talk to you about Corinne.

11:10.880 --> 11:12.712
I mean, she won't answer
my telephone calls.

11:12.920 --> 11:14.957
She won't talk to me
and she won't see me.

11:15.160 --> 11:18.278
Is she all right?
Is my little girl happy?

11:18.480 --> 11:22.713
Oh, happy. Oh, is she happy.
She's so happy, Jess, and I'm happy.

11:22.920 --> 11:24.752
We're both happy.
We couldn't be happier.

11:24.960 --> 11:28.476
You know, she's changed my life.
I am now a one-woman man.

11:28.680 --> 11:30.672
Really?
Jessica, I love her.

11:30.880 --> 11:34.032
Oh, Peter, that's wonderful.

11:34.240 --> 11:36.118
Uh, Peter, I have to
ask you something.

11:36.320 --> 11:38.471
Oh, we're happy, Jess.
Really, really happy...

11:38.680 --> 11:39.830
No, no, not that.

11:40.040 --> 11:41.520
[WHISPERS]
Could I use the bathroom?

11:41.720 --> 11:43.632
No. Absolutely not. Sorry.

11:43.840 --> 11:46.355
Why?
Well, it's a mess.

11:46.560 --> 11:49.678
Uh, the bathroom's a mess.
That doesn't matter, Peter.

11:49.880 --> 11:52.156
I had wine for lunch.
But you can't.

11:52.360 --> 11:54.352
Well, I have to.
Well, then, uh...

11:54.560 --> 11:56.677
Let me clean it up.
It will just take a second.

11:56.880 --> 11:59.520
I just... I want it to be
nice and neat for you, okay?

11:59.720 --> 12:01.837
Just wait one second.

12:03.600 --> 12:04.875
Hi.

12:05.080 --> 12:07.231
Let me guess, you have
a few minutes. Forget it.

12:07.440 --> 12:12.799
No. Listen, do you think
you could do me a favour and,
uh, climb out the window?

12:13.000 --> 12:15.435
Climb out the window? I love it.

12:15.640 --> 12:17.871
There's only one thing that would
make me climb out the window,

12:18.080 --> 12:21.039
and that would be if the
French Riviera was on the other side.

12:21.240 --> 12:23.600
So listen, you can forget about
your window climbing, kiddo.

12:23.680 --> 12:25.000
How about in the shower?
Peter.

12:25.200 --> 12:26.759
Just for a second, please.
Peter.

12:28.600 --> 12:30.273
Okay, babe. It's all ready for you.

12:30.480 --> 12:32.199
Nice, neat and clean there.
Don't be long.

12:32.400 --> 12:33.959
JESSICA:
No, no, I won't.

12:34.160 --> 12:36.197
Thank you.

12:36.400 --> 12:39.438
Oh, poor thing.

12:39.640 --> 12:42.519
I'll bet nobody ever
gives you a drink.

12:42.720 --> 12:47.237
Well, Jessica will give you
a little drink here.

12:47.600 --> 12:52.356
Oh, too fat. Well, you sit right here
and I'll put the chair under...

12:52.560 --> 12:54.119
Here.

13:16.720 --> 13:18.712
What are you doing here,
Mrs. Fine?

13:18.920 --> 13:20.320
Voting.

13:26.560 --> 13:29.234
I know what you're doing here,
Mrs. Fine.

13:29.440 --> 13:30.999
Please, please, Mrs. Tate.

13:31.200 --> 13:33.032
I know we're... We're not friends.

13:33.240 --> 13:38.031
I've always had a hard time
relating to people who
cut the crust off their bread.

13:38.240 --> 13:41.233
But I like you. So please,
don't tell my husband.

13:41.440 --> 13:43.432
Oh, I can't believe this.

13:43.640 --> 13:47.350
Peter's lied to me and he's taken
my little girl away from her home,

13:47.560 --> 13:49.631
and he's cheating with you.

13:49.840 --> 13:54.790
Well, your daughter's very cute,
Mrs. Tate, but I'm not
exactly sheep dip.

13:56.480 --> 13:59.154
Goodbye, Mrs. Tate.
Goodbye, Mrs. Fine.

14:05.760 --> 14:08.400
Lady plumber.
I forgot she was in there.

14:08.600 --> 14:10.557
You lied to me.

14:10.760 --> 14:12.672
And you're cheating on Corinne.

14:12.880 --> 14:16.396
I could kill you.
Oh, come on.

14:16.600 --> 14:18.557
[♪♪♪]

14:21.000 --> 14:22.753
[♪♪♪]

14:29.640 --> 14:32.439
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
Turn the page, you dummy.

14:32.840 --> 14:35.150
I can't believe it.
Jodie's got a date with a girl.

14:35.360 --> 14:38.353
Jodie and a girl.
Do you know what this could mean?

14:38.560 --> 14:42.031
It means she's gonna take
a cold shower, that's what it means.

14:43.440 --> 14:46.751
I'm so excited. Mary, how can you sit
there like nothing's happening?

14:46.960 --> 14:47.960
Jodie's got a date.

14:48.160 --> 14:51.232
Burt, it's nice. But it doesn't have
to mean anything, you know.

14:51.440 --> 14:53.477
Mary, are you kidding?

14:53.680 --> 14:56.400
Once he finds out
how soft and round they are...

14:56.600 --> 15:01.516
Soft and round, huh?
Give him a doughnut.
At least that he can dunk in his coffee.

15:04.240 --> 15:07.392
Hey, no, wait. Let me see.
Let me see. Let me...

15:08.560 --> 15:10.074
You'd better change that shirt.

15:10.280 --> 15:11.839
What's wrong with my shirt?

15:12.040 --> 15:13.440
It's pink.

15:13.640 --> 15:14.835
It's not pink.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.952
Jodie, please. That's a pink shirt.

15:17.160 --> 15:20.119
Burt, it's not pink. It's shrimp.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.198
Some might call it peach.

15:22.400 --> 15:24.710
Don't you have anything
in a plaid? Or brown, huh?

15:24.920 --> 15:27.196
Come on. Nice, strong brown.

15:27.400 --> 15:29.039
I'm wearing this shirt, Burt.

15:29.240 --> 15:32.916
Okay, fine. You wanna be the guy in
the shrimp shirt, that's okay with me.

15:33.120 --> 15:36.318
I mean, I wouldn't wanna be the guy
in the shrimp or the peach shirt.

15:36.520 --> 15:38.398
Come here. Now listen to me.

15:38.600 --> 15:42.913
I know a great French restaurant,
Chez Antoine's.

15:43.120 --> 15:47.194
Very romantic. So dark,
you gotta feel around for your food.

15:47.400 --> 15:50.359
You take her there.
You take her there.
Now, pay attention to me, please.

15:50.560 --> 15:52.119
I just wanna give you a few tips.

15:52.320 --> 15:54.789
Burt, what's the big deal?
I'm just going out for dinner.

15:55.000 --> 15:56.957
No, Jodie. You got a date.

15:57.160 --> 15:58.435
Burt, I know what to do.

15:58.640 --> 16:01.553
You eat, you talk,
preferably not at the same time.

16:02.680 --> 16:05.070
After. What about after?

16:05.280 --> 16:09.194
He's a fruit.
What's gonna happen after?

16:09.760 --> 16:10.830
Shut up, Bob.

16:11.040 --> 16:15.478
I mean, he'll drop her off,
go downstairs,
and fall in love with the doorman.

16:17.040 --> 16:19.396
Hold on. All right, listen.
Listen to me.

16:19.600 --> 16:23.389
You wear some of this stuff.
I guarantee it'll knock her dead.

16:23.600 --> 16:25.353
"Grunt"?

16:27.360 --> 16:28.635
Great stuff.

16:28.840 --> 16:31.230
They have to call it Grunt.

16:31.440 --> 16:34.274
It's terrific. I wore it on
the first date with your mother.

16:34.480 --> 16:35.880
She clung to me all night.

16:36.080 --> 16:38.675
Of course I did.
He took me ice skating.

16:39.800 --> 16:43.111
No, Mary, after.
Remember, huh, after?

16:43.320 --> 16:46.597
Ice skating, on our first date.
I couldn't believe it.

16:46.800 --> 16:50.680
There I was, dressed in black taffeta,
and he takes me ice skating.

16:50.880 --> 16:52.758
The next day, I could hardly walk.

16:53.760 --> 16:55.433
That's right.

16:58.040 --> 16:59.918
From the ice skating, Burt.

17:00.120 --> 17:01.839
Yes, yeah, fine.

17:03.600 --> 17:05.955
All right, now this is
a big thing to remember.

17:06.160 --> 17:09.118
When a girl says no,
she means yes.

17:09.319 --> 17:11.675
Really?
Yeah. Well, it's a well-known fact.

17:11.880 --> 17:14.156
Burt.
Mary, please, this is man talk.

17:14.359 --> 17:17.114
So in other words, if I say,
"Hey, would you like some wine?"

17:17.319 --> 17:19.960
And she says, "No,"
I should order it anyway, hm?

17:23.640 --> 17:25.551
No, I mean after.

17:25.760 --> 17:27.955
I mean, at her apartment.

17:29.480 --> 17:32.359
Oh, at her apartment.
That's right.

17:32.560 --> 17:35.280
Now you know what I'm talking about?
Sure.

17:35.480 --> 17:37.836
So when I say,
"Hey, would you like me to leave?"

17:38.040 --> 17:40.953
And she says, "No," I should go.

17:41.160 --> 17:42.514
Bye.

17:42.800 --> 17:44.359
[♪♪♪]

17:44.560 --> 17:46.677
Jodie. Jodie.

17:48.760 --> 17:50.274
[KNOCKING]

17:53.160 --> 17:56.392
Corinne. You all right?
I got here as fast as I could.

17:56.600 --> 17:58.717
You said suicide.
I nearly had a heart attack.

17:58.920 --> 18:01.320
Corinne, you can't do it.
It's a sin throwing away your life.

18:01.520 --> 18:03.955
What did you take, pills? What?
Nothing.

18:04.160 --> 18:06.595
Come on. How many did you take?
Let me see the bottle.

18:06.800 --> 18:10.191
I didn't take anything. I swear,
all I have on me is a Dristan.

18:10.400 --> 18:13.791
Corinne, how in the world
were you gonna kill yourself
with a Dristan?

18:14.000 --> 18:16.799
I wasn't going to kill myself
with a Dristan.

18:17.000 --> 18:21.000
Corinne, I rushed over here
like a maniac when you called up and
said you were going to kill yourself.

18:21.080 --> 18:23.436
I said I felt like killing myself.

18:23.640 --> 18:27.190
Corinne, are you or are you not
planning on killing yourself?

18:27.400 --> 18:29.073
I guess not.
Are you sure?

18:29.280 --> 18:30.280
Yeah.
Goodbye.

18:30.480 --> 18:32.312
Oh, Tim, please don't go.

18:32.520 --> 18:36.639
Don't go? Corinne, this is a motel.

18:36.840 --> 18:40.754
A motel with mirrors
and furry pillows.
I gotta get out of here.

18:42.320 --> 18:43.320
What is it?

18:43.480 --> 18:45.233
[WHISPERING]
You won't believe
who I saw checking in.

18:45.440 --> 18:46.669
Who?

18:46.880 --> 18:49.600
And look who he's checking in with.
And he's married.

18:49.800 --> 18:52.190
But not to her because
she's married to the...

18:52.400 --> 18:55.711
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
And this guy never has
anything to confess.

19:00.240 --> 19:01.469
Do you love it?

19:01.680 --> 19:05.435
His biggest confession is taking home
paper clips from the office.

19:05.640 --> 19:08.678
Now look what he's taking home
from the office.

19:08.880 --> 19:11.793
Tim, I don't know what to do.

19:12.400 --> 19:14.153
She doesn't know what to do.

19:14.360 --> 19:16.238
I'm a priest in the Pussycat Motel,

19:16.440 --> 19:20.798
surrounded by parishioners
in the parking lot,
and she doesn't know what to do.

19:21.840 --> 19:24.674
I have no place to go,
nowhere to live.

19:24.880 --> 19:26.872
Corinne, what are you talking about?

19:27.080 --> 19:30.232
Tonight, when I went back
to my apartment,

19:30.440 --> 19:33.035
I found Peter there
with another woman.

19:33.240 --> 19:36.438
Oh, no.
I don't know what to do, Tim.

19:36.640 --> 19:38.757
I'm so upset, I could kill him.

19:38.960 --> 19:41.475
Kill? Corinne, that's a sin.

19:41.680 --> 19:43.876
I gotta get out of here.
Oh, please don't go.

19:44.080 --> 19:45.992
You're the only one I can talk to.

19:46.200 --> 19:49.477
Corinne, I'm a priest.
And look where I am.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.600
I mean, do you know
what kind of a place this is?

19:51.760 --> 19:54.150
Look at it. Wall-to-wall bed.

19:54.360 --> 19:56.238
MAID:
Evening.

19:56.440 --> 19:58.193
Oh, hi there.
Time to turn down the bed.

19:58.400 --> 20:02.314
Oh, don't bother. I'm just here,
uh, checking the Bibles.

20:04.040 --> 20:06.191
Look, you have a bible
right here, yes.

20:06.400 --> 20:08.357
See, I check them.
I make sure they're here.

20:08.560 --> 20:11.234
Please, mister, what you wanna do
is your own business.

20:11.440 --> 20:13.318
You work here, you see everything.

20:13.520 --> 20:17.400
We got a dentist, comes in
once a week as Little Bo Peep.

20:18.320 --> 20:21.154
We got a bus driver,
he's King Kong.

20:21.360 --> 20:25.320
Believe me, your outfit is nothing.
Original, but not big.

20:25.520 --> 20:28.354
Hey, you don't...
You don't seem to understand.

20:28.560 --> 20:29.960
I'm really a priest.

20:30.160 --> 20:34.074
Pleasure to meet you, Father.
I'm Joan of Arc.

20:34.280 --> 20:35.475
I got a call...

20:35.680 --> 20:37.797
Listen, you don't know
what goes on in these rooms.

20:38.000 --> 20:41.471
And wait, next month
they're putting in movies.

20:41.680 --> 20:44.639
I don't know.
Me, I go home to my husband.

20:44.840 --> 20:48.800
The fanciest we ever get
is we open our eyes.

20:52.720 --> 20:54.518
Have a nice evening.

20:57.240 --> 20:59.709
She could have been a parishioner,
do you know that?

20:59.920 --> 21:02.719
That was a terrific story.
Checking Bibles.

21:02.920 --> 21:06.277
Yeah. I'm sure God was
real thrilled with that one.

21:06.480 --> 21:09.120
He's up there chuckling over
Flotsky's clever story.

21:09.320 --> 21:11.596
Forgive me. I'm leaving, Corinne.

21:11.800 --> 21:14.759
Tim, I don't know what to do.
What am I gonna do?

21:14.960 --> 21:16.713
Did you pay for the room?

21:16.920 --> 21:19.230
Lock the door and go to sleep.

21:21.200 --> 21:22.839
Corinne, I'll call you.

21:23.040 --> 21:25.714
We can arrange to meet and talk.

21:25.920 --> 21:30.233
In the park, at the zoo, but not here.

21:30.440 --> 21:33.239
I can't take this. I can't even listen.

21:33.440 --> 21:37.070
All I can hear is my heart pounding.
Good night, Corinne.

21:37.280 --> 21:39.840
But I can't sleep here,
all my things are at Peter's.

21:43.240 --> 21:45.277
Oh, I could kill Peter.

21:45.480 --> 21:47.233
[♪♪♪]

21:47.960 --> 21:49.110
[DOOR CLOSES]

21:49.440 --> 21:50.999
Corinne?

21:52.280 --> 21:54.272
Babe, is that you?

21:55.440 --> 21:57.397
Jessica.

21:58.920 --> 22:00.718
Marcia?

22:01.280 --> 22:02.350
[DOOR SLAMS]

22:02.560 --> 22:04.836
Okay, who's there?

22:06.360 --> 22:09.159
Ellen, I know you're aggravated
but you've made your point.

22:09.360 --> 22:11.317
[GUNSHOTS]

22:12.680 --> 22:14.637
[♪♪♪]

22:17.960 --> 22:19.440
You...

22:26.880 --> 22:31.033
